1	//! Round-4 probe-pinned unit tests for the three corpus-scale rule-rendering
2	//! blockers surfaced by the open-side full-corpus measurement.
3	//!
4	//!  * Blocker 1 — the SAPIC `process="…"` rule attribute: rendered
5	//!    DOUBLE-quoted, between `color` and `no_derivcheck`, value verbatim
6	//!    (probe:p_process, target:ct).
7	//!  * Blocker 2 — a multi-line last element makes the enclosing delimiter drop
8	//!    or not depending on the operator: a MULTISET-UNION `)` drops to its own
9	//!    line at the `(` column (like the round-3 AC fix), while an APPLICATION
10	//!    `)` stays JOINED as `>)` (probe:uniondrop / probe:appdrop).
11	//!  * Blocker 3 — a huge `variants (modulo AC)` block (C8/BP_IBS reach ~10 000
12	//!    lines) renders without stack overflow on a production-sized stack: the
13	//!    Doc build (`reduce_*`), render (`lay`) and DROP are all iterative.
14	//!
15	//! The byte-exact expectations for blockers 1–2 are sliced straight from the
16	//! probe captures (round2/targets/*.hs.txt); the fixtures below reconstruct the
17	//! AST the renderer must turn back into those bytes. The captures self-skip
18	//! once the crate moves at integration (the corpus gate takes over).
