1	//! R3 tests — restriction / lemma / formula rendering.
2	//!
3	//! Two layers, mirroring rounds 1–2:
4	//!  1. Probe-pinned unit tests: hand-written fixtures asserted against
5	//!     byte-exact oracle output (probe captures under
6	//!     workspace/scratchpad/probes/, provenance `probe:<name>`).
7	//!  2. Whole-block parity over the round-3 curated corpus captures
8	//!     (round3/targets/*.hs.txt): every restriction block and every lemma
9	//!     block of every file is parsed back into the crate's AST by a
10	//!     layout-insensitive echo parser (test harness only — it discards all
11	//!     whitespace, so layout can only come from the renderer) and
12	//!     re-rendered; the bytes must match the capture. Guarded-comment
13	//!     content and embedded proof scripts are opaque inputs and are carried
14	//!     verbatim (they are NOT produced by this crate).
